# Browsing the Web 

ISP - Internet Service Provider 
 -> DNS - Domain Name Service (Essentially a phone book)
 -has all the URL's and sends back the address. So it responds back through ISP the 
 -IP location and pulls up the website we're looking for 

 -Our own IP address gets sent to the google servers (or whatever website you're
 -looking at)
 - That website will no how to send you items back (such as a waitor getting the food
 - you ordered). The "food" that gets sent back is HTML, CSS and JavaScript. 


